At the World Diabetic Centre, World Diabetes Day is commemorated with a multitude of educational initiatives and community outreach programs. The Centre hosts informative seminars, workshops, and health screenings to raise awareness about diabetes prevention, management, and treatment. Additionally, they collaborate with healthcare professionals, researchers, and advocacy groups to advance diabetes research and improve patient care. Through their dedication, the Centre strives to empower individuals with the knowledge and resources needed to lead healthier lives, while also advocating for policy changes to address the global diabetes epidemic. Together, they work towards a future where diabetes is better understood, prevented, and effectively managed worldwide. Click to learn more https://www.worlddiabetescentre.com/publicsite?pid=aditiclinic&page=world-diabetes-day
